		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Pogrom</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">Not to be confused with <a href="/wiki/Pogromni" title="Pogromni" class="mw-redirect">Pogromni</a>, the volcano in the Aleutian Islands.</div>
<p>A <b>pogrom</b> is a form of <a href="/wiki/Riot" title="Riot">riot</a> directed against a particular group, whether ethnic, religious, or other, and characterized by the killing and destruction of their homes, businesses, and religious centers. The term in English is often used to denote extensive <a href="/wiki/Violence" title="Violence">violence</a> against <a href="/wiki/Jew" title="Jew">Jews</a> — either spontaneous or premeditated — but it has also been applied to similar incidents against other minority groups.</p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:282px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Hep-hep_riots.jpg" class="image" title="Hep-Hep riots in Frankfurt, 1819. On the left, two peasant women are assaulting a Jewish man with pitchfork and broom. On the right, a man wearing spectacles, tails, and a six-button waistcoat, &quot;perhaps a pharmacist or a schoolteacher,&quot;[1] holds another Jewish man by the throat and is about to club him with a truncheon. A contemporary engraving by Johann Michael Voltz."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Hep-hep_riots.jpg/280px-Hep-hep_riots.jpg" width="280" height="223" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Hep-hep_riots.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="/wiki/Hep-Hep_riots" title="Hep-Hep riots">Hep-Hep riots</a> in Frankfurt, 1819. On the left, two peasant women are assaulting a Jewish man with pitchfork and broom. On the right, a man wearing spectacles, tails, and a six-button waistcoat, "perhaps a pharmacist or a schoolteacher,"<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> holds another Jewish man by the throat and is about to club him with a truncheon. A contemporary engraving by Johann Michael Voltz.</div>
</div>
</div>
