<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFMenocal2003"><a href="/wiki/Mar%C3%ADa_Rosa_Menocal" title="María Rosa Menocal">Menocal, María Rosa</a> (April 2003), <i>The Ornament of the World: How Muslims, Jews and Christians Created a Culture of Tolerance in Medieval Spain</i>, Back Bay Books, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0316168718" class="internal">ISBN 0316168718</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Ornament+of+the+World%3A+How+Muslims%2C+Jews+and+Christians+Created+a+Culture+of+Tolerance+in+Medieval+Spain&amp;rft.aulast=Menocal&amp;rft.aufirst=Mar%C3%ADa+Rosa&amp;rft.au=Menocal%2C+Mar%C3%ADa+Rosa&amp;rft.date=April+2003&amp;rft.pub=Back+Bay+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0316168718&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Pogrom"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
